The African Centre for Leadership, Strategy and Development (Centre LSD) will on Saturday in Abuja graduate its 10th set of 50 students. A statement, yesterday, by Mr. Amodu Lawal, Senior Programme Officer of the centre said the 10th graduation ceremony which also doubles as 10th annual lecture is organized in partnership with Konrad Adeneuar Stftung (KAS) and would be chaired by Barr. Allen Onyema, Chief Executive Officer of Air Peace. He said Yemi Mapaderun, Registrar, Nigeria Air force School of Finance and Accounts, Badagry, will be the guest speaker, adding that dignitaries expected at the event include the Governor of Ekiti State, Dr Kayode Fayemi, Senator Ovie Omo Agege, Hon. Francis Waive, members of the diplomatic Corps, and donor community. “The event will climax with the presentation of certificate to graduating students and taking of matriculation oath by the 65 newly admitted students. “This year’s graduation brings the total number of change agents trained by the centre through the Leadership School to 681,” Lawal said. Centre LSD graduates 50 ‘Change Agents’ leaders in Abuja MTN Foundation holds 10th graduation ceremony Centre graduates 25 women in Suleja